http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Jatha-taken-out-against-child-marriages/article14016807.ece

A jatha was taken out in Koppal to create awareness against child marriages on Saturday.Sri Gavisiddeshwar Swami of Gavi Mutt in Koppal, who had organised the jatha, in association with UNICEF,district administration as part of the annual Sri Gavisiddeshwar fair, said that such jathas would be a annual feature to create awareness among people to eradicate the deep rooted social evil system.A large number of students from various schools and colleges had participated in the jatha, holding placards and shouting slogans against child marriages,